  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening District Capacity to Rapidly Detect, Confirm and Investigate All Suspected Cases of COVID-19 at Points of Entry and Adjacent Communities</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Uganda is now in phase 4 of the COVID-19 pandemic characterized by widespread community transmission. Overall, 29,361 COVID-19 cases have been confirmed by 16th December. The Government of Uganda with support from UN and other partners, responded promptly to the outbreak through actions guided by the National COVID-19 Response Plan March 2020 &#x2013; March 2021. These include the following priority sectors of intervention: coordination and leadership, risk communication, surveillance and community engagement and sub pillars including the PoE working group. The prioritisation exercise conducted by the UN Health Thematic Working Group, identified the need to integrate the preparedness and response for COVID-19 and Cholera in all program activities and highlighted the following priorities aligned with the MOH response plans: coordination and leadership; risk communication and community engagement; case management; logistics, supplies and surveillance.</narrative>
  </description>
